> Time for a pizza party right in your own kitchen—no delivery required!

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 475 degrees.
Wash and dry produce.

Sprinkle 1-2 TBSP @flour{2%tbsp} over a clean work surface. Remove
@pizza dough{4} from packaging and place on floured surface. Shape each
piece of dough into a ball.

> TIP: Spray your hands with nonstick cooking spray or dust with flour
> to prevent sticking.

Evenly sprinkle another 1-2 TBSP flour on top of dough balls. Cover with a
clean #kitchen towel{} and let rest at room temperature, ~{20%minutes}.

While dough rests, halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}. Core, deseed,
and dice @green bell pepper{1} into 1-inch pieces. Trim and discard root
ends from @baby lettuce{2}; chop leaves into bite-size pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a medium, preferably nonstick,
#pan over medium heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until
browned and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @sugar{1%tsp} and a splash of @water{}; cook, stirring occasionally,
until caramelized, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once dough has rested 20 minutes, line two #baking sheets{} with
#parchment paper{}. Press and stretch one dough ball into an oval shape;
place on one side of a prepared baking sheet. Repeat with three more dough
balls (arrange so there are two dough ovals per sheet).

> For 8 servings, stretch remaining four dough balls into oval shapes and
> return to floured surface; sprinkle tops lightly with flour and cover
> with a clean kitchen towel.

Cover baking sheets with clean #kitchen towels{}; let dough rest
~{15%minutes}.

Once dough has rested 15 minutes, lightly flour hands. Press and stretch
dough on sheets into larger oval shapes, about 10 inches long and 6 inches
wide.

> For 8, leave dough on surface while topping and baking first batch.

Spread dough with @marinara sauce{14%oz}; sprinkle with
@mozzarella cheese{2%cup}. Top with as much caramelized onion,
bell pepper, and @pepperoni{3.5%oz} as you like.

Bake pizzas on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway
through, until crust is golden, ~{14-18%minutes}.

> For 8 servings, transfer baked pizzas to a cutting board. Repeat with
> remaining dough.

While pizzas bake, combine @garlic powder{1%tsp} and
@butter{2%tbsp} in a small #microwave safe bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap
and microwave until butter has melted, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir to combine.

> Use 4 TBSP butter for 8 servings.

Once pizzas are done, remove from oven. Brush edges of crust with garlic
butter to taste. Grate @Parmesan cheese block{1} over pizzas, then cut
each pizza into eight slices.

In a large #bowl, toss lettuce, @shredded carrots{4%oz},
and @creamy balsamic dressing{3%oz} until combined. Lightly season with
salt and pepper.

Divide pizzas and salad between plates in separate sections. Serve with
@chili flakes{1%tsp} for sprinkling and @buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%oz}
for dipping.